---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

// YMYL Safety FAQs and Legal Disclaimers
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is a Tenants in Common (TIC) agreement?",
    answer: "Tenants in Common (TIC) is a legal property deed structure that allows two or more people to own unequal shares of a property. Unlike Joint Tenancy (where ownership must be split 50/50 and automatically passes to the other owner upon death), TIC allows you to detail precise ownership percentages (e.g., 70/30) and leave your share to a designated heir through a will. Unmarried co-buyers should almost always use a TIC structure combined with a written co-ownership contract."
  },
  {
    question: "How does the equity split shift if we pay mortgage payments equally?",
    answer: "If Partner A pays 100% of the down payment, but both partners split the monthly mortgage payment 50/50, the equity split shifts over time. Initially, Partner A owns 100% of the home equity at closing. However, as Partner B contributes 50% of the monthly principal paydown, Partner B is acquiring equity. Over 15 or 30 years, Partner B's equity percentage will slowly climb, while Partner A's percentage will decrease from 100% toward a lower balance."
  },
  {
    question: "Do capital improvements affect our ownership share?",
    answer: "Yes, if one partner pays for a major capital improvement (like a $20,000 roof replacement or kitchen remodel), it increases the home's value. A co-ownership agreement should specify whether that partner receives a dollar-for-dollar credit to their equity share, or if the cost is split. This planner allows you to configure how capital improvements are credited."
  }
];
---

<Layout 
  title="Co-Buying Mortgage Equity Splitter & Legal Term Planner"
  description="Calculate dynamic home equity ownership percentages for unmarried partners or friends buying a house with unequal contributions, and plan legal Tenants in Common exit rules."
  canonicalUrl="/co-buying-equity-splitter"
>
  <Header activeSlug="equity-splitter" />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-10 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-10 flex-grow">
    <!-- Header Section -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h1 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-text-main sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl tracking-tight">
        Co-Buying Mortgage <span class="text-brand-accent">Equity Splitter & Legal Planner</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-text-muted max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
        Unmarried couples or friends buying a home together often make unequal financial contributions. This tool models how home equity splits shift year-over-year as mortgage principal is paid down, and helps outline critical legal exit and buyout terms.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- AdSense Notice and Safety Banner -->
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-warning/30 bg-warning/5 p-4 text-xs text-text-muted space-y-2 leading-relaxed">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 font-bold text-warning">
        <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
        </svg>
        <span>Consumer Advisory & Disclaimer</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This application is a mathematical modeling and outlining tool. It does not constitute legal advice, representation, or a binding legal contract. Real estate statutes, title deed requirements, and cohabitation laws vary substantially by state and county. We strongly recommend that all co-buyers review the agreement blueprint generated by this tool with a licensed local family law attorney or real estate attorney before closing. All data stays client-side.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Dashboard Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
      
      <!-- LEFT: Inputs (Contributions & Exit Rules) (7 Cols) -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 space-y-6">
        
        <!-- Loan & Property parameters -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border-subtle bg-bg-card p-5 space-y-4 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="font-display text-sm font-semibold text-text-main flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-brand-primary text-bg-main text-3xs font-bold">1</span>
            Property & Mortgage Details
          </h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
            <div class="space-y-1.5">
              <label for="price-input" class="text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted">Purchase Price</label>
              <div class="relative">
                <span class="absolute left-3 top-2 text-xs text-text-muted">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="price-input" value="400000" class="h-9 w-full rounded border border-border-input bg-bg-input pl-6 pr-2 text-xs text-text-main font-bold font-tabular focus:outline-none" />
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1.5">
              <label for="rate-input" class="text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted">Interest Rate</label>
              <div class="relative">
                <input type="number" id="rate-input" value="6.5" step="0.1" class="h-9 w-full rounded border border-border-input bg-bg-input px-3 text-xs text-text-main font-bold font-tabular focus:outline-none" />
                <span class="absolute right-3 top-2 text-xs text-text-muted">%</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1.5">
              <label for="term-select" class="text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted">Loan Term</label>
              <select id="term-select" class="h-9 w-full rounded border border-border-input bg-bg-input px-3 text-xs text-text-main font-bold focus:outline-none cursor-pointer">
                <option value="30">30-Year Fixed</option>
                <option value="15">15-Year Fixed</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Partner Financial Contributions -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border-subtle bg-bg-card p-5 space-y-5 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="font-display text-sm font-semibold text-text-main flex items-center gap-2 border-b border-border-subtle pb-3">
            <span class="flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-brand-primary text-bg-main text-3xs font-bold">2</span>
            Co-Buyer Financial Contributions
          </h2>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <!-- Partner A -->
            <div class="space-y-4 p-4 rounded-lg bg-blue-500/5 border border-blue-500/10">
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-500 block">Buyer A (e.g. Partner 1)</span>
              
              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <label for="dp-a-input" class="text-3xs font-bold text-text-muted uppercase">Down Payment Contribution</label>
                <div class="relative">
                  <span class="absolute left-2.5 top-1 text-xs text-text-muted">$</span>
                  <input type="number" id="dp-a-input" value="60000" class="h-8 w-full rounded border border-border-input bg-bg-input pl-5 pr-2 text-xs font-tabular text-text-main focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <div class="flex justify-between text-3xs font-bold text-text-muted uppercase">
                  <span>Mortgage Payment Share</span>
                  <span id="mort-a-display" class="text-blue-500">50%</span>
                </div>
                <input type="range" id="mort-a-slider" min="0" max="100" value="50" class="w-full" />
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Partner B -->
            <div class="space-y-4 p-4 rounded-lg bg-pink-500/5 border border-pink-500/10">
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-pink-500 block">Buyer B (e.g. Partner 2)</span>
              
              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <label for="dp-b-input" class="text-3xs font-bold text-text-muted uppercase">Down Payment Contribution</label>
                <div class="relative">
                  <span class="absolute left-2.5 top-1 text-xs text-text-muted">$</span>
                  <input type="number" id="dp-b-input" value="10000" class="h-8 w-full rounded border border-border-input bg-bg-input pl-5 pr-2 text-xs font-tabular text-text-main focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <div class="flex justify-between text-3xs font-bold text-text-muted uppercase">
                  <span>Mortgage Payment Share</span>
                  <span id="mort-b-display" class="text-pink-500">50%</span>
                </div>
                <input type="range" id="mort-b-slider" min="0" max="100" value="50" class="w-full" />
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Legal Term Options -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border-subtle bg-bg-card p-5 space-y-4 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="font-display text-sm font-semibold text-text-main flex items-center gap-2 border-b border-border-subtle pb-3">
            <span class="flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-brand-primary text-bg-main text-3xs font-bold">3</span>
            Co-Ownership Exit & Buyout Rules
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted">
            <!-- Buyout Trigger Notice -->
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-2 border-b border-border-subtle pb-3">
              <div class="space-y-0.5">
                <span class="text-text-main block">Exit / Buyout Notice Period</span>
                <span class="text-3xs text-text-muted font-normal block">Time a partner has to buy out the other before forced sale of the property.</span>
              </div>
              <select id="notice-select" class="h-8 w-36 rounded border border-border-input bg-bg-input px-2 text-xs text-text-main focus:outline-none cursor-pointer">
                <option value="60 Days">60 Days</option>
                <option value="90 Days" selected>90 Days (Recommended)</option>
                <option value="120 Days">120 Days</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <!-- Home Valuation Method -->
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-2 border-b border-border-subtle pb-3">
              <div class="space-y-0.5">
                <span class="text-text-main block">Fair Market Valuation Method</span>
                <span class="text-3xs text-text-muted font-normal block">How the buyout home value is established if partners disagree.</span>
              </div>
              <select id="valuation-select" class="h-8 w-52 rounded border border-border-input bg-bg-input px-2 text-xs text-text-main focus:outline-none cursor-pointer">
                <option value="Average of Two Independent Appraisals" selected>Average of Two Appraisals (Recommended)</option>
                <option value="Single Jointly Selected Appraisal">Single Joint Appraisal</option>
                <option value="Purchase Price adjusted for CPI inflation">Purchase Price + Inflation Index</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <!-- Capital Improvement Credits -->
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-2">
              <div class="space-y-0.5">
                <span class="text-text-main block">Capital Improvement Credits</span>
                <span class="text-3xs text-text-muted font-normal block">How renovations over $2,000 are accounted for in equity shifts.</span>
              </div>
              <select id="renovation-select" class="h-8 w-52 rounded border border-border-input bg-bg-input px-2 text-xs text-text-main focus:outline-none cursor-pointer">
                <option value="Added to the contributing buyer's equity seed" selected>Equity Seed Credit (Recommended)</option>
                <option value="Split equally regardless of contributor">Split 50/50 Automatically</option>
                <option value="No equity credit unless mutually agreed">No Credit / Subject to Agreement</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- RIGHT: Equity Scorecard & Blueprint Document (5 Cols) -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-5 space-y-6 lg:sticky lg:top-20">
        
        <!-- Current Equity Split Scorecard -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border-subtle bg-bg-card p-5 space-y-5 shadow-md">
          <h2 class="font-display text-sm font-semibold text-text-main border-b border-border-subtle pb-2">Equity Split Timeline</h2>
          
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="p-3 bg-blue-500/5 border border-blue-500/20 rounded-lg text-center">
              <span class="text-4xs text-text-muted font-bold block uppercase">Buyer A Equity Share</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-extrabold text-blue-500 font-tabular block" id="share-a-year-0">--%</span>
              <span class="text-4xs text-text-muted block mt-1" id="share-a-year-30">Shift to --% in Year 30</span>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 bg-pink-500/5 border border-pink-500/20 rounded-lg text-center">
              <span class="text-4xs text-text-muted font-bold block uppercase">Buyer B Equity Share</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-extrabold text-pink-500 font-tabular block" id="share-b-year-0">--%</span>
              <span class="text-4xs text-text-muted block mt-1" id="share-b-year-30">Shift to --% in Year 30</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between text-xs font-semibold">
              <span class="text-text-muted">Down Payment Split:</span>
              <span id="dp-split-text" class="font-bold text-text-main">--% / --%</span>
            </div>
            <div id="shift-insight" class="text-3xs text-text-muted leading-relaxed bg-bg-main p-3 rounded-lg border border-border-subtle">
              Calculating equity shift metrics...
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Trust & Will Affiliate Integration -->
          <div class="border-t border-border-subtle pt-4 space-y-3">
            <div class="text-3xs text-text-muted font-semibold leading-relaxed">
              * Secure your co-ownership legally. Create custom estate planning and cohabitation wills online.
            </div>
            <a 
              href="https://trustandwill.com/" 
              target="_blank" 
              rel="noopener noreferrer" 
              class="w-full inline-flex h-9 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 text-white font-bold text-xs shadow-sm hover:shadow transition-all text-center"
            >
              Generate Cohabitation Deeds (Trust & Will)
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Legal Blueprint Document Card -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border-subtle bg-bg-card p-5 space-y-4 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-display text-sm font-semibold text-text-main flex items-center justify-between border-b border-border-subtle pb-2">
            <span>Agreement Blueprint Worksheet</span>
            <button 
              id="copy-blueprint-btn" 
              class="text-4xs font-bold text-brand-accent hover:text-brand-accent-hover focus:outline-none transition-colors border border-brand-accent/20 px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-brand-accent/5 hover:bg-brand-accent/10 cursor-pointer"
            >
              Copy Blueprint
            </button>
          </h3>

          <p class="text-3xs text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Copy this outline. It incorporates your calculated dynamic equity splits and selected exit rules, formatted to present to your real estate lawyer.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-bg-input rounded-lg border border-border-subtle p-3 font-mono text-4xs text-text-main whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed max-h-72 overflow-y-auto cursor-text select-all" id="blueprint-container">
            Outlining legal blueprint parameters...
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Educational Resource Content (Topical Authority & SEO Defensibility) -->
    <div class="border-t border-border-subtle pt-10 space-y-6">
      <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-text-main sm:text-xl">
        Unmarried Couples Home Purchasing Guide: Safeguarding Joint Assets
      </h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-xs sm:text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-text-main">The Difference: Tenants in Common vs. Joint Tenancy</h3>
          <p>
            When purchasing a home as unmarried partners or friends, how you hold title is critically important:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-2 space-y-1">
            <li><strong>Joint Tenancy with Right of Survivorship (JTWROS):</strong> Owners hold equal 50% shares. If one owner passes away, their share automatically transfers to the surviving owner. It bypasses wills. This is the default structure for married couples but can be risky for unmarried buyers or friends.</li>
            <li><strong>Tenants in Common (TIC):</strong> Allows unequal ownership ratios (e.g. 80/20) matching the actual financial contributions. If an owner passes away, their share does NOT go to the other owner; instead, it goes to their designated heirs via their will.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-text-main">Why a Written Cohabitation Agreement is Mandatory</h3>
          <p>
            Unlike divorce laws, which provide a structured framework for dividing assets when a marriage dissolves, there is no standard legal code for separating assets when unmarried co-buyers break up. Without a written agreement, any disputes will likely result in expensive litigation (Partition Lawsuits) where a judge orders a forced sale of the house, and all proceeds are eaten up by legal fees.
          </p>
          <p>
            A written TIC agreement details the buyout option, notice times, appraisal mechanics, and capital improvement tracking upfront, keeping you out of court.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
    <div class="border-t border-border-subtle pt-10 space-y-6">
      <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-text-main sm:text-xl">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <dl class="space-y-6 max-w-4xl">
        {faqs.map(faq => (
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <dt class="font-display text-sm font-semibold text-text-main">{faq.question}</dt>
            <dd class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">{faq.answer}</dd>
          </div>
        ))}
      </dl>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script>
  // DOM Elements
  const priceInput = document.getElementById('price-input') as HTMLInputElement;
  const rateInput = document.getElementById('rate-input') as HTMLInputElement;
  const termSelect = document.getElementById('term-select') as HTMLSelectElement;

  const dpAInput = document.getElementById('dp-a-input') as HTMLInputElement;
  const mortASlider = document.getElementById('mort-a-slider') as HTMLInputElement;
  const mortADisplay = document.getElementById('mort-a-display');

  const dpBInput = document.getElementById('dp-b-input') as HTMLInputElement;
  const mortBSlider = document.getElementById('mort-b-slider') as HTMLInputElement;
  const mortBDisplay = document.getElementById('mort-b-display');

  const noticeSelect = document.getElementById('notice-select') as HTMLSelectElement;
  const valuationSelect = document.getElementById('valuation-select') as HTMLSelectElement;
  const renovationSelect = document.getElementById('renovation-select') as HTMLSelectElement;

  const shareAYear0 = document.getElementById('share-a-year-0');
  const shareAYear30 = document.getElementById('share-a-year-30');
  const shareBYear0 = document.getElementById('share-b-year-0');
  const shareBYear30 = document.getElementById('share-b-year-30');

  const dpSplitText = document.getElementById('dp-split-text');
  const shiftInsight = document.getElementById('shift-insight');
  const blueprintContainer = document.getElementById('blueprint-container');
  const copyBlueprintBtn = document.getElementById('copy-blueprint-btn');

  // Slider Synchronization
  mortASlider.addEventListener('input', () => {
    mortBSlider.value = String(100 - parseInt(mortASlider.value));
    updateSlidersDisplay();
    calculateEquitySplit();
  });

  mortBSlider.addEventListener('input', () => {
    mortASlider.value = String(100 - parseInt(mortBSlider.value));
    updateSlidersDisplay();
    calculateEquitySplit();
  });

  function updateSlidersDisplay() {
    if (mortADisplay) mortADisplay.textContent = `${mortASlider.value}%`;
    if (mortBDisplay) mortBDisplay.textContent = `${mortBSlider.value}%`;
  }

  function calculateEquitySplit() {
    const price = parseFloat(priceInput.value) || 0;
    const rate = parseFloat(rateInput.value) || 0;
    const termYears = parseInt(termSelect.value) || 30;

    const dpA = parseFloat(dpAInput.value) || 0;
    const dpB = parseFloat(dpBInput.value) || 0;
    const totalDp = dpA + dpB;

    const shareAPayPercent = parseFloat(mortASlider.value) / 100;
    const shareBPayPercent = parseFloat(mortBSlider.value) / 100;

    // Underwriting Loan Amount
    const loanAmount = price - totalDp;

    // Standard Amortization Math to find principal paydown at end of loan
    // Monthly rate
    const r = (rate / 100) / 12;
    const n = termYears * 12;

    let monthlyPI = 0;
    if (r > 0) {
      monthlyPI = (loanAmount * r * Math.pow(1 + r, n)) / (Math.pow(1 + r, n) - 1);
    } else {
      monthlyPI = loanAmount / n;
    }

    // Dynamic Equity Share splits
    // Year 0 Equity is just down payment contribution split
    let shareAYear0Pct = 0;
    let shareBYear0Pct = 0;

    if (totalDp > 0) {
      shareAYear0Pct = (dpA / totalDp) * 100;
      shareBYear0Pct = (dpB / totalDp) * 100;
    } else {
      shareAYear0Pct = shareAPayPercent * 100;
      shareBYear0Pct = shareBPayPercent * 100;
    }

    // Cumulative principal paid down at end of loan (Year 30 or 15) is equal to full loanAmount
    // Buyer A's total equity contribution over full duration = dpA + (loanAmount * shareAPayPercent)
    // Buyer B's total equity contribution over full duration = dpB + (loanAmount * shareBPayPercent)
    const totalEquityCap = totalDp + loanAmount; // equivalent to purchase price
    const buyerAEndEquity = dpA + (loanAmount * shareAPayPercent);
    const buyerBEndEquity = dpB + (loanAmount * shareBPayPercent);

    const shareAYear30Pct = totalEquityCap > 0 ? (buyerAEndEquity / totalEquityCap) * 100 : 0;
    const shareBYear30Pct = totalEquityCap > 0 ? (buyerBEndEquity / totalEquityCap) * 100 : 0;

    // Display updates
    if (shareAYear0) shareAYear0.textContent = `${shareAYear0Pct.toFixed(1)}%`;
    if (shareBYear0) shareBYear0.textContent = `${shareBYear0Pct.toFixed(1)}%`;
    if (shareAYear30) shareAYear30.textContent = `Shifts to ${shareAYear30Pct.toFixed(1)}% in Yr ${termYears}`;
    if (shareBYear30) shareBYear30.textContent = `Shifts to ${shareBYear30Pct.toFixed(1)}% in Yr ${termYears}`;

    if (dpSplitText) {
      const dpASplit = totalDp > 0 ? (dpA / totalDp) * 100 : 0;
      const dpBSplit = totalDp > 0 ? (dpB / totalDp) * 100 : 0;
      dpSplitText.textContent = `${dpASplit.toFixed(0)}% / ${dpBSplit.toFixed(0)}%`;
    }

    // Insight messaging
    if (shiftInsight) {
      const shiftSize = Math.abs(shareAYear0Pct - shareAYear30Pct);
      if (shiftSize > 5) {
        shiftInsight.innerHTML = `⚠️ Dynamic equity shift detected. Due to unequal down payment splits, Buyer A's ownership starts at <strong>${shareAYear0Pct.toFixed(1)}%</strong> but shifts by <strong>${shiftSize.toFixed(1)}%</strong> over the loan life as mortgage payments are split <strong>${mortASlider.value}/${mortBSlider.value}</strong>.`;
      } else {
        shiftInsight.innerHTML = `✅ Balanced ownership model. Financial contributions are matched and equity percentages remain stable throughout the <strong>${termYears}-year</strong> lifecycle.`;
      }
    }

    // Generate Legal Blueprint Document
    updateAgreementBlueprint(shareAYear0Pct, shareAYear30Pct, shareBYear0Pct, shareBYear30Pct, totalDp, loanAmount);
  }

  function updateAgreementBlueprint(aStart: number, aEnd: number, bStart: number, bEnd: number, totalDp: number, loan: number) {
    if (!blueprintContainer) return;

    const notice = noticeSelect.value;
    const valuation = valuationSelect.value;
    const renovation = renovationSelect.value;
    const termYears = termSelect.value;

    blueprintContainer.innerHTML = `CO-OWNERSHIP AGREEMENT BLUEPRINT & TIC WORKSHEET

PARTIES:
Buyer A (Partner 1): [Buyer A Name]
Buyer B (Partner 2): [Buyer B Name]

PROPERTY ADDRESS: [Property Address]
ESTIMATED PURCHASE PRICE: $${(parseFloat(priceInput.value) || 0).toLocaleString()}

1. EQUITY OWNERSHIP RATIO (DYNAMIC SLIDING MODEL)
The parties agree to hold title as Tenants in Common (TIC) with ownership shares determined by actual cash and debt servicing contributions. 
- INITIAL EQUITY SPLIT (At Closing - Year 0):
  * Buyer A Share: ${aStart.toFixed(1)}%
  * Buyer B Share: ${bStart.toFixed(1)}%
- TERM TARGET EQUITY SPLIT (Year ${termYears} of Amortization):
  * Buyer A Share: ${aEnd.toFixed(1)}%
  * Buyer B Share: ${bEnd.toFixed(1)}%
- DYNAMIC FORMULA:
  At any given date of sale or buyout, equity percentages shall be computed retrospectively as:
  Party Equity Share % = (Party Down Payment + Party Cumulative Principal Payments) / (Total Down Payment + Total Principal Paid)

2. MONTHLY EXPENSE DISTRIBUTION:
- Mortgage Debt Service (P&I): split ${mortASlider.value}% (Buyer A) / ${mortBSlider.value}% (Buyer B)
- Property Taxes & Insurance: split ${mortASlider.value}% (Buyer A) / ${mortBSlider.value}% (Buyer B)
- Maintenance & Repairs: split 50% / 50% unless otherwise agreed in writing.

3. EXIT & BUYOUT PROVISIONS:
- NOTICE PERIOD: If either partner wishes to exit the agreement, they must provide a written notice of intent. The non-exiting partner has a ${notice} buyout election period to purchase the exiting partner's share.
- APPRAISAL METHOD: Fair market value of the property for buyout calculations shall be determined by: "${valuation}".
- CAPITAL IMPROVEMENT ADJUSTMENT: For any renovation exceeding $2,000 paid by one party, the cost shall be: "${renovation}".

4. RESIDENCY DISSOLUTION DISPUTE RESOLUTION:
If the non-exiting partner fails to execute a buyout within the notice window, the property shall be listed on the open market with a licensed real estate broker, and both parties agree to execute all sale documents. Net proceeds shall be divided strictly in accordance with the calculated equity split ratio at the date of listing.

DISCLAIMER: THIS IS A PRE-LEGAL WORKSHEET. PLEASE BRING THIS DOCUMENT TO A LICENSED REAL ESTATE ATTORNEY TO DRAFT A BINDING TENANTS IN COMMON CONTRACT.`;
  }

  // Bind change listeners to all elements
  priceInput.addEventListener('input', calculateEquitySplit);
  rateInput.addEventListener('input', calculateEquitySplit);
  termSelect.addEventListener('change', calculateEquitySplit);
  dpAInput.addEventListener('input', calculateEquitySplit);
  dpBInput.addEventListener('input', calculateEquitySplit);
  noticeSelect.addEventListener('change', calculateEquitySplit);
  valuationSelect.addEventListener('change', calculateEquitySplit);
  renovationSelect.addEventListener('change', calculateEquitySplit);

  // Copy Blueprint Action
  if (copyBlueprintBtn && blueprintContainer) {
    copyBlueprintBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const text = blueprintContainer.textContent || "";
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
        const originalText = copyBlueprintBtn.textContent;
        copyBlueprintBtn.textContent = "Copied!";
        copyBlueprintBtn.classList.replace('text-brand-accent', 'text-success');
        setTimeout(() => {
          copyBlueprintBtn.textContent = originalText;
          copyBlueprintBtn.classList.replace('text-success', 'text-brand-accent');
        }, 1500);
      });
    });
  }

  // Run initial calculations
  updateSlidersDisplay();
  calculateEquitySplit();
</script>
